, is a species of fern in the family Dryopteridaceae. The Williams' glade fern has been used in traditional medicine to treat various health conditions, including fever, inflammation, and respiratory issues, due to its potential anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. Bioactive constituents of this plant include flavonoids, alkaloids, and phenolic acids, which contribute to its medicinal properties. The Williams' glade fern is commonly used to make teas and infusions, as well as being incorporated into traditional herbal remedies, such as decoctions and tinctures."}